partial_orders.reason: Both edits are modifying the exact same function `test_from_datetime64_raises()`. Edit 0 renames the function to `test_from_datetime64_freq_changes()`, while Edit 1 changes the function body from testing that an exception is raised to testing the actual behavior with assertions. These edits reference the same function symbol and are part of a single refactoring task - converting a test that expects an exception to a test that verifies the actual functionality. The function name change and body change are mechanically linked as part of updating this single test function, making either edit naturally prompt the other as the next step in the same micro-task.
